The sudden murder of a female student identified as Deborah Samuel of Shehu Shagari College of Education in Sokoto State has sent shock waves across the country. According to reports, she was allegedly murdered for blasphemy. However, many top Nigeria figures have reacted to this news by airing their individual views.
The Imam of the National Mosque in Abuja, Professor Ibrahim Maqari took to his Twitter handle to say that the Muslims have redlines and should not be crossed. Hence, alleging that the grievances of Deborah’s killers weren’t addressed. This tweet caught the attention of Adeola Fayehun, a Nigerian Journalist as she asked if Deborah’s killers reported their grievances before attacking the deceased.According to Adeola Fayehun via her verified Twitter handle: “The Imam of the National Mosque in Abuja, professor Ibrahim Maqari said their grievances were not addressed. The question is, did they report their grievances before the execution? No! Hence, justice for Deborah”.


